'''codon'''
{{wikipedia}}
# {{biochemistry}} a [[sequence]] of three [[adjacent]] [[nucleotide]]s, which [[encode]] for a specific [[amino acid]] during [[protein]] synthesis, or [[translation]]. Three special codons, called "[[stop codon]]s," signal protein synthesis to terminate.  
 
